[[Category:Toxicology]]
{{biology-stub}}

This is a '''list of the full [[palette (computing)|color palettes]]''' for notable [[video game console]] hardware.
For each unique palette, an image color test chart and sample image ([[True Color|Truecolor]] original follows) rendered with that palette (without [[dither]]ing) are given. The test chart shows the full 8-bits, 256 levels of the red, green and blue ([[RGB color model|RGB]]) primary colors and cyan, magenta and yellow complementary colors, along with a full 8-bits, 256 levels grayscale. Gradients of RGB intermediate colors (orange, lime green, sea green, sky blue, violet and fuchsia), and a full [[hue]]'s spectrum are also present. Color charts are not [[Gamma correction|gamma]] corrected.
:{| style="border-style: none" border="0" cellpadding="0" |- | [[File:RGB 24bits palette sample image.jpg]] | [[File:RGB 24bits palette color test chart.png]] |}
==Atari==
===Atari 2600=== {{see also|Television Interface Adaptor}} The [[Atari 2600]] used different [[YIQ]] color palettes dependent on the television signal format used.<ref>Atari 2600 [http://www.biglist.com/lists/stella/archives/200109/msg00285.html "TIA color chart"]. {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/5wRXhh2Zn?url=http://www.biglist.com/lists/stella/archives/200109/msg00285.html |date=February 12, 2011 }}</ref>
====NTSC==== With the [[NTSC]] format, a 128-color palette was available, built based on eight [[luminance]] values and 15 combinations of Pb and Pr [[Chrominance|chroma]] signals (plus Pb&nbsp;=&nbsp;Pr&nbsp;=&nbsp;0 for a pure [[grayscale]]):
:{| | [[File:Atari2600 NTSC palette sample image.png]] | [[File:Atari2600 NTSC palette color test chart.png]] | style="vertical-align:top;" | [[File:Atari2600 NTSC palette.png]] |}
